projects.description:
Solution for the transportation authorities of the city of Dallas so that they can collect, connect and monitor real-time data in a protected environment. The web application provides an overview of all traffic lights, cameras and variable traffic signs on a city map. If you click on an item, you will see a live feed of the item, such as live camera feeds or the color of the traffic light. You have an overview of active alarms and an option to perform an action. The web application is connected to the backend via the secure Rest API. The backend application is responsible for the device data and authentication and was connected to 3pp systems via Adapters. The solution works in the Azure Government Cloud. (Respond, NodeJS, Active Directory, Azure, MongoDB)

Responsibilities:
❖ Role as a SAFe-Product Owner;
❖ Managing a team of 9 employees in Minsk (Belarus);
❖ Designing the architecture of back-end and front-end modules (eg Permissions, actions, data layer);
❖ Documentation of the architecture;
❖ Give presentations;
❖ Provide daily stand-up;
❖ Provide stakeholders with sprint demos;
❖ Technical workshops with 3pp and customer.

Web application that showcases the possibilities of the Ericsson DDM 2.0 IOT platform at the most important Telecom congress for Ericsson Mobile World Congress. Web application showed an overview of all IoT devices at the conference on a map and a live feed of the sensor data (e.g. temperature). If a Sensor triggered an alarm it was displayed on the map. Demo was used for various sales activities after the conference. Solution based on the demo has been sold to Japanese operator (React, CSS, Rest, Azure Web Application)

Responsibilities:
❖ Determine feasibility;
❖ Determining the minimum feasible scope;
❖ Make prototype;
❖ Then make the demo in Ericsson branding;
❖ Installing the demo in Azure;
❖ Giving support during the conference.

Project for the development of the API Orchestrator and Data Broker part of the Ericsson IoT Platform. Service that allows developers to host a REST API made in NodeJs. The Data Broker can receive data via MQTT, COAP and automatically store the data in a NoSQL database that the developer can read via the REST API. (NodeJS, Swagger, Docker, MQTT (VerneMQ), COAP (Ponte), NoSQL (CouchDB), Linux, VM)

Responsibilities:
❖ Helping the team, which had been working for half a year, to get back on track;
❖Solution Architect for the API Orchestrator and Data Broker;
❖ Translate platform requirements to the architecture of the API Orchestrator and Data Broker;
❖ Documentation of architecture and interfaces;
❖ Manage team as Product Owner;
❖ Writing user stories;
❖ Coordinate with other development teams;
❖ Coordination with other stakeholders (eg security, hosting, sales)
❖ Give demos to stakeholders and customers.

As part of a proposal for an ITS solution for the management of city buses and mobile payments for the city of Kigali in Rwanda, a demo was made. As part of the demo, the Ericsson ITS solution was linked to 3pp Bus management system and Ericsson mobile payment solution. The demo showed the location of the bus and the number of payments in a web portal. The demo was given at the Transform Africa Summit. (HTML, Javascript, CSS, REST, SOAP, Java, NoSQL, JBOSS, Linux)

Responsibilities:
❖ Collecting information from third parties.
❖ Determining the minimum attainable scope;
❖ Design and implementation of the demo backend and web application;
❖ Install and configure the software on the servers;
❖ Install special hardware in a bus in Rwanda and connect it to the demo;
❖ Presentation of the demo to visitors of the Ericsson stand at the "Transform Africa Summit";
❖ Demo given to President of Rwanda.

